  "prompt": "How do you say goodbye to a dying loved one?",
  "response": "Saying goodbye to a dying loved one can be an incredibly emotional and challenging experience. Here are some suggestions on how to approach it:\n\n1. **Be Present**: Simply being present can provide comfort. Hold their hand or sit quietly with them, allowing for moments of silence.\n\n2. **Express Your Feelings**: Share your feelings, memories, and what they mean to you. Let them know how much they are loved and cherished.\n\n3. **Acknowledge Their Journey**: If appropriate, acknowledge the journey they are on. You might say something like, \"It's okay to let go,\" or \"You are loved and will be missed.\"\n\n4. **Share Memories**: Reminiscing about special moments you shared can bring warmth and connection. It also allows you to celebrate their life.\n\n5. **Offer Comfort**: If they are open to it, you can offer physical comfort, such as a gentle touch or a soothing presence.\n\n6. **Encourage Their Wishes**: Invite them to express any wishes they might have regarding their final moments or their legacy.\n\n7. **Use Music or Readings**: Sometimes playing their favorite music or reading poems or passages that are meaningful to both of you can provide solace.\n\n8. **Be Honest About Your Feelings**: It\u2019s okay to let them see your sadness. You can express that you will miss them but also reassure them that it\u2019s okay to move on.\n\n9. **Create a Goodbye Ritual**: If it feels right, create a small ritual, whether it\u2019s lighting a candle, sharing a prayer, or simply saying \u201cgoodbye\u201d in your own way.\n\n10. **Follow Your Instincts**: Every relationship is different. Trust your instincts about what feels right in the moment.\n\nUltimately, the most important thing is to be genuine and to convey your love and support during this difficult time.",
